JOHANNESBURG – December salaries as well as outstanding bonuses will be paid as planned on 22 December, arms firm Denel revealed in a statement on Friday. READ: Calls for Denel to come clean on its finances The comments come on the back of a week of intense endearments about liquidity challenges with shareholder representatives, the Department of Public Enterprises and National Treasury. In confirming the successful outcome of talks, Denel Chief Financial Officer Odwa Mhlwana said the company would continue paying suppliers. “I also want to thank them [suppliers] for being patient with us at times when we were not able to honour our obligations. We are also thankful to our employees for their patience and understanding during these past two weeks”, Mhlwana added. eNCA